  "elapsed_s": 2.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we can back to Zhmerinka with the train.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "As we came back to Zhmerinka, the people over there, they were already talking, everybody was talking that the Russians already-- this was already 1944.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the beginning, like January, February, and the Red Army already took, I think, Kiev.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they're closing in, closer and closer on Vinnitsa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And by the way, in 1943, I didn't mention that, Hitler came to Vinnitsa to give orders.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "When [?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Stalingrad-- ?] in 1940, when [?",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Stalingrad ?] was formed, his headquarters was in Vinnitsa.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And because he came to Vinnitsa, they killed in Vinnitsa 30,000 to 40,000 Jews just before he came also in graves, in the out-- outskirts of Vinnitsa, which was a couple of graves and also in Odessa.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "In Odessa was killed maybe 50,000 or 60,000.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "In Zhytomyr, I was Zhytomyr, was killed about 30,000 and Berdychiv.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "In the Ukraine was killed millions, maybe a million and a half, maybe more.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But they never mentioned actually so much were the Jews in Ukraine were all murdered that they mention so much about concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But what about that the rest of the Jews?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "From the Russian Jews, Romanian Jews, which did not go to concentration but in the ghettos and so on and so on.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So there were graves.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There are graves in every town, in every city, from-- from the Polish border up to Kharkiv, up to Kiev, all over into [?",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Smudens, ?] Jewish graves in the Ukraine, which they don't even know where the graves because the Russians built buildings on these graves.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So when I-- when we were in Zhmerinka, we knew already something is going to happen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Russians are closing.",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
